### 2.2 Drone Controller — [controller.py](file:///home/ubuntu/githubrepos/dronesim/drone_controller/controller.py)

This is the per-drone "brain". Each of the 4 controller containers runs its own instance.

#### Architecture Pattern: Async/Sync Bridge

```mermaid
graph LR
    FLASK["Flask Thread<br/>(synchronous)"] -->|"asyncio.Queue"| MAVSDK["MAVSDK Event Loop<br/>(async)"]
    MAVSDK -->|"result dict"| FLASK
    MAVSDK -->|"UDP MAVLink"| PX4["PX4 SITL"]
```

- **Main thread**: Runs `asyncio.run(main())` — the MAVSDK event loop.
- **Background thread**: Flask REST API on port `500x`.
- **Bridge**: `send_command()` pushes a dict onto `asyncio.Queue`, then busy-waits (max 10s) for `result["done"] = True`.

#### Telemetry Monitors (8 concurrent coroutines)

| Coroutine | Data Source | Stored Field |
|---|---|---|
| `_monitor_position` | `drone.telemetry.position()` | `lat`, `lon`, `alt` |
| `_monitor_battery` | `drone.telemetry.battery()` | `battery_percent`, `battery_voltage` |
| `_monitor_flight_mode` | `drone.telemetry.flight_mode()` | `flight_mode` |
| `_monitor_armed` | `drone.telemetry.armed()` | `armed` |
| `_monitor_velocity` | `drone.telemetry.velocity_ned()` | `ground_speed` |
| `_monitor_gps` | `drone.telemetry.gps_info()` | `gps_fix_type`, `gps_num_satellites` |
| `_monitor_heading` | `drone.telemetry.heading()` | `heading_deg` |
| `_monitor_mission_progress` | `drone.mission.mission_progress()` | `mission_progress` (e.g. `"5/100"`) |

#### REST API Endpoints

| Method | Route | Action |
|---|---|---|
| `GET` | `/telemetry` | Returns full telemetry snapshot |
| `GET` | `/status` | Quick health check |
| `GET` | `/logs` | Returns log buffer (with `?since=N`) |
| `POST` | `/arm` | Arms motors |
| `POST` | `/disarm` | Disarms motors |
| `POST` | `/takeoff` | Sets altitude and takes off |
| `POST` | `/land` | Lands at current position |
| `POST` | `/rtl` | Returns to launch |
| `POST` | `/mission/upload` | Clears mission, uploads waypoints (×50 for looping) |
| `POST` | `/mission/start` | Auto-arms and starts uploaded mission |
| `POST` | `/mission/pause` | Pauses mission execution |

#### Continuous Patrol Loop

When the GCS uploads waypoints (e.g. 2 waypoints), `controller.py` multiplies them ×50 to create 100 MAVSDK `MissionItem`s. This forces the drone to loop through the patrol path indefinitely until the GCS commands RTL.

```python
# controller.py line 262
waypoints = waypoints * 50  # Creates continuous patrol loop
```

